        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think I would find it surprising if a cimported include file ended up behind local declarations. It seems more intuitive if (transitively) cimported declarations came in one block, rather than being subject to the early-late split. As a module author, I do not control cimports, so their declarations shouldn't interfere with my code. (And now you are going to tell me that that breaks your use case, right?)\r\n\r\nIn any case, all I really want is a solution that:\r\n- avoids breaking existing code (if possible)\r\n- makes it clear where the order comes from\r\n- makes it easy and obvious to repair code that misbehaves under the new semantics\r\n\r\nIMHO, the current implementation provides none of those three.",
